first, you need to clone this repo
```bash
yum install -y git
git clone https://github.com/mod96/Mmumshad-CKA.git
```
or,
```bash
apt-get install -y git
git clone https://github.com/mod96/Mmumshad-CKA.git
```
by running `.bash` file, you'll install `containerd`(cri - docker runtime), `kubelet`, `kubeadm`, `kubectl`, `kubernetes-cni`.

Before doing any further, you need to add DNS records for all nodes. For example,
```
192.168.0.9 master.k8s
192.168.0.10 node1.k8s
...
```

Then, for master node, run `kubeadm-init.bash`.